The paper discusses the use of influence diagrams for decision-making, which is a topic commonly studied in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also presents an algorithm for determining the relevant past in decision-making, which involves computational methods and data structures (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper discusses the structure of decision scenarios and the conditions necessary for them to be well-defined, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT) and mathematical analysis (cs.MA).
